#: ../../../topics/images.rst:5
msgid "Downloading Item Images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:9
msgid ""
"Scrapy provides an :doc:`item pipeline </topics/item-pipeline>` for "
"downloading images attached to a particular item, for example, when you "
"scrape products and also want to download their images locally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:13
msgid ""
"This pipeline, called the Images Pipeline and implemented in the :class:"
"`ImagesPipeline` class, provides a convenient way for downloading and "
"storing images locally with some additional features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:17
msgid "Convert all downloaded images to a common format (JPG) and mode (RGB)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:18
msgid "Avoid re-downloading images which were downloaded recently"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:19 ../../../topics/images.rst:152
msgid "Thumbnail generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:20
msgid "Check images width/height to make sure they meet a minimum constraint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:22
msgid ""
"This pipeline also keeps an internal queue of those images which are "
"currently being scheduled for download, and connects those items that arrive "
"containing the same image, to that queue. This avoids downloading the same "
"image more than once when it's shared by several items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:27
msgid ""
"`Pillow`_ is used for thumbnailing and normalizing images to JPEG/RGB "
"format, so you need to install this library in order to use the images "
"pipeline. `Python Imaging Library`_ (PIL) should also work in most cases, "
"but it is known to cause troubles in some setups, so we recommend to use "
"`Pillow`_ instead of `PIL <Python Imaging Library>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:37
msgid "Using the Images Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:39
msgid ""
"The typical workflow, when using the :class:`ImagesPipeline` goes like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:42
msgid ""
"In a Spider, you scrape an item and put the URLs of its images into a "
"``image_urls`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:45
msgid "The item is returned from the spider and goes to the item pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:47
msgid ""
"When the item reaches the :class:`ImagesPipeline`, the URLs in the "
"``image_urls`` field are scheduled for download using the standard Scrapy "
"scheduler and downloader (which means the scheduler and downloader "
"middlewares are reused), but with a higher priority, processing them before "
"other pages are scraped. The item remains \"locked\" at that particular "
"pipeline stage until the images have finish downloading (or fail for some "
"reason)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:54
msgid ""
"When the images are downloaded another field (``images``) will be populated "
"with the results. This field will contain a list of dicts with information "
"about the images downloaded, such as the downloaded path, the original "
"scraped url (taken from the ``image_urls`` field) , and the image checksum. "
"The images in the list of the ``images`` field will retain the same order of "
"the original ``image_urls`` field. If some image failed downloading, an "
"error will be logged and the image won't be present in the ``images`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:64
msgid "Usage example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:66
msgid ""
"In order to use the image pipeline you just need to :ref:`enable it <topics-"
"images-enabling>` and define an item with the ``image_urls`` and ``images`` "
"fields::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:70
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"class MyItem(scrapy.Item):\n"
"\n"
"    # ... other item fields ...\n"
"    image_urls = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    images = scrapy.Field()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:78
msgid ""
"If you need something more complex and want to override the custom images "
"pipeline behaviour, see :ref:`topics-images-override`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:84
msgid "Enabling your Images Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:88
msgid ""
"To enable your images pipeline you must first add it to your project :"
"setting:`ITEM_PIPELINES` setting::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:91
msgid "ITEM_PIPELINES = {'scrapy.contrib.pipeline.images.ImagesPipeline': 1}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:93
msgid ""
"And set the :setting:`IMAGES_STORE` setting to a valid directory that will "
"be used for storing the downloaded images. Otherwise the pipeline will "
"remain disabled, even if you include it in the :setting:`ITEM_PIPELINES` "
"setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:97 ../../../topics/images.rst:162
#: ../../../topics/images.rst:201
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:99
msgid "IMAGES_STORE = '/path/to/valid/dir'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:102
msgid "Images Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:104
msgid ""
"File system is currently the only officially supported storage, but there is "
"also (undocumented) support for `Amazon S3`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:110
msgid "File system storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:112
msgid ""
"The images are stored in files (one per image), using a `SHA1 hash`_ of "
"their URLs for the file names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:115
msgid "For example, the following image URL::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:117
msgid "http://www.example.com/image.jpg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:119
msgid "Whose `SHA1 hash` is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:121
msgid "3afec3b4765f8f0a07b78f98c07b83f013567a0a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:123
msgid "Will be downloaded and stored in the following file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:125
msgid "<IMAGES_STORE>/full/3afec3b4765f8f0a07b78f98c07b83f013567a0a.jpg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:127 ../../../topics/images.rst:174
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:129
msgid ""
"``<IMAGES_STORE>`` is the directory defined in :setting:`IMAGES_STORE` "
"setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:131
msgid ""
"``full`` is a sub-directory to separate full images from thumbnails (if "
"used). For more info see :ref:`topics-images-thumbnails`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:135
msgid "Additional features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:138
msgid "Image expiration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:142
msgid ""
"The Image Pipeline avoids downloading images that were downloaded recently. "
"To adjust this retention delay use the :setting:`IMAGES_EXPIRES` setting, "
"which specifies the delay in number of days::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:146
msgid ""
"# 90 days of delay for image expiration\n"
"IMAGES_EXPIRES = 90"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:154
msgid ""
"The Images Pipeline can automatically create thumbnails of the downloaded "
"images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:159
msgid ""
"In order use this feature, you must set :setting:`IMAGES_THUMBS` to a "
"dictionary where the keys are the thumbnail names and the values are their "
"dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:164
msgid ""
"IMAGES_THUMBS = {\n"
"    'small': (50, 50),\n"
"    'big': (270, 270),\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:169
msgid ""
"When you use this feature, the Images Pipeline will create thumbnails of the "
"each specified size with this format::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:172
msgid "<IMAGES_STORE>/thumbs/<size_name>/<image_id>.jpg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:176
msgid ""
"``<size_name>`` is the one specified in the :setting:`IMAGES_THUMBS` "
"dictionary keys (``small``, ``big``, etc)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:179
msgid "``<image_id>`` is the `SHA1 hash`_ of the image url"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:183
msgid ""
"Example of image files stored using ``small`` and ``big`` thumbnail names::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:185
msgid ""
"<IMAGES_STORE>/full/63bbfea82b8880ed33cdb762aa11fab722a90a24.jpg\n"
"<IMAGES_STORE>/thumbs/small/63bbfea82b8880ed33cdb762aa11fab722a90a24.jpg\n"
"<IMAGES_STORE>/thumbs/big/63bbfea82b8880ed33cdb762aa11fab722a90a24.jpg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:189
msgid "The first one is the full image, as downloaded from the site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:192
msgid "Filtering out small images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:198
msgid ""
"You can drop images which are too small, by specifying the minimum allowed "
"size in the :setting:`IMAGES_MIN_HEIGHT` and :setting:`IMAGES_MIN_WIDTH` "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:203
msgid ""
"IMAGES_MIN_HEIGHT = 110\n"
"IMAGES_MIN_WIDTH = 110"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:206
msgid "Note: these size constraints don't affect thumbnail generation at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:208
msgid "By default, there are no size constraints, so all images are processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:213
msgid "Implementing your custom Images Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:218
msgid ""
"Here are the methods that you should override in your custom Images Pipeline:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:224
msgid ""
"As seen on the workflow, the pipeline will get the URLs of the images to "
"download from the item. In order to do this, you must override the :meth:"
"`~get_media_requests` method and return a Request for each image URL::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:229
msgid ""
"def get_media_requests(self, item, info):\n"
"    for image_url in item['image_urls']:\n"
"        yield scrapy.Request(image_url)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:233
msgid ""
"Those requests will be processed by the pipeline and, when they have "
"finished downloading, the results will be sent to the :meth:"
"`~item_completed` method, as a list of 2-element tuples. Each tuple will "
"contain ``(success, image_info_or_failure)`` where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:238
msgid ""
"``success`` is a boolean which is ``True`` if the image was downloaded "
"successfully or ``False`` if it failed for some reason"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:241
msgid ""
"``image_info_or_error`` is a dict containing the following keys (if success "
"is ``True``) or a `Twisted Failure`_ if there was a problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:244
msgid ""
"``url`` - the url where the image was downloaded from. This is the url of "
"the request returned from the :meth:`~get_media_requests` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:248
msgid ""
"``path`` - the path (relative to :setting:`IMAGES_STORE`) where the image "
"was stored"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:251
msgid "``checksum`` - a `MD5 hash`_ of the image contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:253
msgid ""
"The list of tuples received by :meth:`~item_completed` is guaranteed to "
"retain the same order of the requests returned from the :meth:"
"`~get_media_requests` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:257
msgid "Here's a typical value of the ``results`` argument::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:259
msgid ""
"[(True,\n"
"  {'checksum': '2b00042f7481c7b056c4b410d28f33cf',\n"
"   'path': 'full/7d97e98f8af710c7e7fe703abc8f639e0ee507c4.jpg',\n"
"   'url': 'http://www.example.com/images/product1.jpg'}),\n"
" (True,\n"
"  {'checksum': 'b9628c4ab9b595f72f280b90c4fd093d',\n"
"   'path': 'full/1ca5879492b8fd606df1964ea3c1e2f4520f076f.jpg',\n"
"   'url': 'http://www.example.com/images/product2.jpg'}),\n"
" (False,\n"
"  Failure(...))]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:270
msgid ""
"By default the :meth:`get_media_requests` method returns ``None`` which "
"means there are no images to download for the item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:275
msgid ""
"The :meth:`ImagesPipeline.item_completed` method called when all image "
"requests for a single item have completed (either finished downloading, or "
"failed for some reason)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:279
msgid ""
"The :meth:`~item_completed` method must return the output that will be sent "
"to subsequent item pipeline stages, so you must return (or drop) the item, "
"as you would in any pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:283
msgid ""
"Here is an example of the :meth:`~item_completed` method where we store the "
"downloaded image paths (passed in results) in the ``image_paths`` item "
"field, and we drop the item if it doesn't contain any images::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:287
msgid ""
"from scrapy.exceptions import DropItem\n"
"\n"
"def item_completed(self, results, item, info):\n"
"    image_paths = [x['path'] for ok, x in results if ok]\n"
"    if not image_paths:\n"
"        raise DropItem(\"Item contains no images\")\n"
"    item['image_paths'] = image_paths\n"
"    return item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:296
msgid "By default, the :meth:`item_completed` method returns the item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:300
msgid "Custom Images pipeline example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:302
msgid ""
"Here is a full example of the Images Pipeline whose methods are examplified "
"above::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/images.rst:305
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"from scrapy.contrib.pipeline.images import ImagesPipeline\n"
"from scrapy.exceptions import DropItem\n"
"\n"
"class MyImagesPipeline(ImagesPipeline):\n"
"\n"
"    def get_media_requests(self, item, info):\n"
"        for image_url in item['image_urls']:\n"
"            yield scrapy.Request(image_url)\n"
"\n"
"    def item_completed(self, results, item, info):\n"
"        image_paths = [x['path'] for ok, x in results if ok]\n"
"        if not image_paths:\n"
"            raise DropItem(\"Item contains no images\")\n"
"        item['image_paths'] = image_paths\n"
"        return item"
msgstr ""
